        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 3:51PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 351 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
line of strong thunderstorms along a line extending from Clinchfield
to near La Crosse, and moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, the leading
edge of this line of storms has also exhibited areas of
localized rotation. A brief tornado could quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Americus, Cochran, Hawkinsville, Vienna, Unadilla, Montezuma,
Byromville, Pineview, Pinehurst, Andersonville, Lilly, Dooling,
Lamar, Hayneville, Browndale, Richwood, Empire, New Era, La Crosse,
and Mobley Crossing.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and west central Georgia.</instruction>
